# Conditional Runner

This project provides a simple command runner that executes a sequence of commands based on conditional logic. It is designed to be easily extensible and customizable for various use cases.

## Installation

To install the project, you can use pip:

```bash
pip install .
```

Make sure you have Python 3.12.9 or higher installed.

## Usage

To run the command sequence, use the installed CLI:

```bash
conditional-runner start
```

Add `--condition` to skip the prompt, for example:

```bash
conditional-runner start --condition first
```

You can customize the commands in the `src/conditional_runner/commands.py` file to suit your needs.

